cells:
Just a heads up: I'm not claiming this is the best method, this is just what I use currently
• 1. Memorize the position of the U/D stickers of the twisted corners
• 2. Execute U/D face position for corner 1 and U/D sticker position for corner 2
• 3. Execute U/D face position for corner 2 and U/D sticker position for corner 1
• E.g: If UFR, UBL and DFL are twisted clockwise, we execute UFR-UBL-LDF and then UFR-DFL-LUB
• If UFR is not one of the twisted corners, we do a y rotation or a U move to put one of the U pieces in place of UFR and do the same
• If none of the 3 twisted corners are on U, we solve them by doing sexy moves and rotating D
• E.g: If DFR, DFL and DBL are twisted clockwise, we do U R U' R' U R U' R' D U R U' R' U R U' R' D U R U' R' U R U' R' D2
